# Same king/rook shuffle position, but a prior search (without history) warms the TT
# with entries for positions in the repetition cycle.  On the subsequent search with
# 6-move history, transpositionTable::pv() used those cached moves to extend the PV
# past the threefold draw.
#
# Bug fixed: pv() re-entered the root hash into the repetition table, double-counting
# it.  The fix uses emptyState() so only successor positions are entered, and checks
# drawn() before pushing the move into pv.moves.  The result is that even with a warm
# TT the PV is truncated at the draw boundary.

ucinewgame
setoption name OwnBook value false
# Warm the TT with a search from the same position but no game history.
position fen 7k/1pp5/pb1p2Bp/4p1rP/PP2P1r1/2PP4/5PP1/R4RK1 w - - 0 1
go depth 9 wait
# Now search with 6-move history.  The warm TT has entries for the shuffle positions.
position fen 7k/1pp5/pb1p2Bp/4p1rP/PP2P1r1/2PP4/5PP1/R4RK1 w - - 0 1 moves g1h1 g4h4 h1g1 h4g4 g1h1 g4h4
go depth 9 wait
# The draw must be recognised: score must be 0 and PV must not extend past it.
expect-count 9 score cp 0.*pv h1g1 h4g4$
expect-count 0 score cp 0.*pv h1g1 h4g4 \S
